13/03/2008
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Newly elected Cypriot President Demetris Christofias and Turkish Cypriot leader Mehmet Ali Talat will meet on March 21st in an effort to resume reunification talks, UN official Jose Diaz announced on Wednesday (March 12th). Negotiations have been stalled since 2004, when the Turkish Cypriots approved -- but the Greek Cypriots rejected -- a reunification plan drafted by then UN Secretary-General Kofi Annan. (AFP, Phileleftheros, RIA Novosti - 12/03/08)
